  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Data minimization is the principle of collecting, processing, and retaining only the personal data that is strictly necessary for a specified purpose. In LLM applications it applies at five distinct stages: what you collect from users, what you inject into model prompts, what the model is allowed to log, what you retain from model outputs, and how long any of this lives in your systems. GDPR Article 5(1)(c) codifies this as a legal requirement for processing data of EU residents."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Data minimization applied at each pipeline stage: collection \u2192 prompt scope \u2192 LLM call \u2192 output filter \u2192 retention"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why Minimization Matters Specifically for LLMs"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "LLMs amplify the privacy risk of over-collected data in two ways:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Prompt memorization",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": providers may log prompts for model improvement. Any PII in a prompt could be stored, reviewed, or potentially recalled in future model versions."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Context leakage",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": in multi-turn conversations, early messages persist in the context window. PII mentioned in turn 1 is visible to the model in turn 10 and may leak into turn 10's response."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The safest data is data you never collected. PII that never enters your pipeline cannot leak from it, cannot appear in logs, cannot be subpoenaed, and does not require redaction, retention management, or breach notification."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Stage 1: Minimize at Collection"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Collect only the fields required for the task. For an LLM customer-service bot that needs to look up an order, the order ID is necessary \u2014 the customer's date of birth is not:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass\nfrom typing import Optional\n\n# Over-collected form (bad): collects everything\n@dataclass\nclass OverCollectedUserProfile:\n    name: str\n    email: str\n    phone: str\n    date_of_birth: str\n    ssn: str\n    address: str\n    order_id: str  # the only field the chatbot actually needs\n\n# Minimized form (good): only what the task requires\n@dataclass\nclass MinimizedChatbotContext:\n    order_id: str\n    first_name: str  # for personalization: 'Hi Alice, your order...'\n    # everything else is looked up server-side via order_id if needed\n\ndef build_context_from_session(session: dict) -> MinimizedChatbotContext:\n    return MinimizedChatbotContext(\n        order_id=session['order_id'],\n        first_name=session.get('first_name', 'there'),\n    )"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Stage 2: Minimize the Prompt"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Even when you hold more data about a user, inject only the fields the model needs for the current turn. A task-scoped prompt ensures that PII not relevant to the task cannot leak into the response:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from anthropic import Anthropic\n\nclient = Anthropic()\n\n# Full user record (held server-side, not in the prompt)\nUSER_RECORD = {\n    'id': 'USR-1234',\n    'first_name': 'Alice',\n    'email': 'alice@example.com',   # not needed for order status\n    'phone': '555-1234',             # not needed for order status\n    'orders': [\n        {'id': 'ORD-9001', 'status': 'shipped', 'eta': '2025-07-05'},\n    ],\n}\n\ndef build_minimized_prompt(user_id: str, query: str) -> list[dict]:\n    user = USER_RECORD  # fetched from DB by user_id\n\n    # Include only what is needed for this specific task\n    order = user['orders'][0]\n    context = (\n        f\"Customer: {user['first_name']}\\n\"\n        f\"Order {order['id']}: {order['status']}, ETA {order['eta']}\"\n    )\n    # email and phone are NOT injected \u2014 model doesn't need them\n\n    return [\n        {'role': 'system', 'content': 'You are an order-status assistant. '\n         'Answer using only the provided order context. '\n         'Never invent order details.'},\n        {'role': 'user', 'content': f'{context}\\n\\nCustomer question: {query}'},\n    ]\n\ndef answer_order_query(user_id: str, query: str) -> str:\n    messages = build_minimized_prompt(user_id, query)\n    response = client.messages.create(\n        model='claude-haiku-4-5-20251001',\n        max_tokens=256,\n        system=messages[0]['content'],\n        messages=messages[1:],\n    )\n    return response.content[0].text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Stage 3: Prompt Logging Policy"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Many LLM providers log prompts for debugging and model improvement by default. Review your provider's data processing terms and opt out where available. When logging prompts internally, apply PII scrubbing before writing to any log store:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import hashlib\nimport re\nimport logging\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\nEMAIL_RE = re.compile(r'[\\w.+\\-]+@[\\w\\-]+\\.[a-z]{2,}', re.I)\nPHONE_RE = re.compile(r'\\b(\\+?1[\\-.\\s]?)?\\(?\\d{3}\\)?[\\-.\\s]?\\d{3}[\\-.\\s]?\\d{4}\\b')\n\ndef scrub_for_log(text: str) -> str:\n    text = EMAIL_RE.sub('[EMAIL]', text)\n    text = PHONE_RE.sub('[PHONE]', text)\n    return text\n\ndef log_llm_call(\n    prompt: list[dict],\n    response: str,\n    user_id: str,\n) -> None:\n    # Hash user_id so logs can be correlated for debugging\n    # without storing the raw identifier\n    user_hash = hashlib.sha256(user_id.encode()).hexdigest()[:12]\n\n    # Scrub PII from prompt before logging\n    scrubbed_prompt = [\n        {**msg, 'content': scrub_for_log(msg.get('content', ''))}\n        for msg in prompt\n    ]\n    scrubbed_response = scrub_for_log(response)\n\n    logger.info(\n        'llm_call user=%s prompt=%s response=%s',\n        user_hash, scrubbed_prompt, scrubbed_response[:200],\n    )"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Stage 4: Output Minimization"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Instruct the model to include only information necessary to answer the user's question, and to avoid echoing back PII from the context. Then scan the output before returning it:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import re\nfrom typing import NamedTuple\n\nSYSTEM_WITH_MINIMIZATION = '''\nYou are a helpful assistant.\nPRIVACY RULES:\n- Include in your response only what is directly needed to answer the question.\n- Do not repeat email addresses, phone numbers, or full names from the context\n  unless the user explicitly asks for them.\n- Do not volunteer personal details beyond what is required.\n'''\n\n# Post-generation scan: remove PII the model echoed back\nPII_IN_OUTPUT = [\n    (re.compile(r'[\\w.+\\-]+@[\\w\\-]+\\.[a-z]{2,}', re.I), '[EMAIL]'),\n    (re.compile(r'\\b(\\+?1[\\-.\\s]?)?\\(?\\d{3}\\)?[\\-.\\s]?\\d{3}[\\-.\\s]?\\d{4}\\b'), '[PHONE]'),\n    (re.compile(r'\\b\\d{3}-\\d{2}-\\d{4}\\b'), '[SSN]'),\n]\n\ndef sanitize_output(text: str) -> str:\n    for pattern, replacement in PII_IN_OUTPUT:\n        text = pattern.sub(replacement, text)\n    return text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Stage 5: Retention Limits and Automated Deletion"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Data that is no longer needed should not be kept. Implement time-to-live policies for conversation histories, prompt logs, and any intermediate data derived from user inputs:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from datetime import datetime, timedelta\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass, field\nfrom typing import Optional\n\n@dataclass\nclass ConversationRecord:\n    session_id: str\n    user_id_hash: str\n    messages: list[dict]\n    created_at: datetime = field(default_factory=datetime.utcnow)\n    retention_days: int = 30\n\n    @property\n    def expires_at(self) -> datetime:\n        return self.created_at + timedelta(days=self.retention_days)\n\n    @property\n    def is_expired(self) -> bool:\n        return datetime.utcnow() > self.expires_at\n\nclass ConversationStore:\n    def __init__(self):\n        self._store: dict[str, ConversationRecord] = {}\n\n    def save(self, record: ConversationRecord) -> None:\n        self._store[record.session_id] = record\n\n    def get(self, session_id: str) -> Optional[ConversationRecord]:\n        record = self._store.get(session_id)\n        if record and record.is_expired:\n            del self._store[session_id]\n            return None\n        return record\n\n    def purge_expired(self) -> int:\n        expired = [sid for sid, r in self._store.items() if r.is_expired]\n        for sid in expired:\n            del self._store[sid]\n        return len(expired)\n\n# In production: run purge_expired() as a scheduled job (cron or celery beat)\n# and persist to a database with TTL indexes (e.g., MongoDB TTL index,\n# Redis EXPIRE, PostgreSQL + pg_cron)."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Contextual Integrity in Conversation Histories"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Multi-turn LLM conversations accumulate context. A user may share sensitive information in turn 3 that they don't intend to remain relevant in turn 20. Apply context windowing and selective summarization to limit PII persistence:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def summarize_old_turns(\n    messages: list[dict],\n    keep_recent: int = 6,\n    summarize_fn = None,\n) -> list[dict]:\n    if len(messages) <= keep_recent:\n        return messages\n\n    old = messages[:-keep_recent]\n    recent = messages[-keep_recent:]\n\n    if summarize_fn:\n        # Use an LLM to summarize old turns (with PII redacted)\n        summary_text = summarize_fn(old)\n    else:\n        summary_text = f'[Previous {len(old)} turns summarized]'\n\n    summary_msg = {\n        'role': 'system',\n        'content': f'Conversation summary (PII removed): {summary_text}',\n    }\n    return [summary_msg] + recent\n\ndef pii_aware_summary(messages: list[dict]) -> str:\n    combined = ' '.join(m.get('content', '') for m in messages)\n    # Scrub PII before passing to summarizer\n    combined_clean = scrub_for_log(combined)\n    # In practice: call an LLM summarizer on combined_clean\n    return f'User asked about {len(messages)} topics (details removed).'"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Data Minimization vs. Model Utility"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Aggressive data minimization can reduce model utility if the model lacks context it needs. The goal is to inject the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "minimum sufficient",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "italic"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " context \u2014 not the minimum possible:"
          }
        ]
      },
